Course: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=F5mRW0jo-U4&ab_channel=freeCodeCamp.org
03h08m

Create virtualenv: virtualenv -p python .

Start virtualenv: source bin/activate

Install Django: pip install django==2.0.7 (It's betetr to use 2.1.5)

Start Django project on current folder: django-admin startproject trydjango .

Test if it worked: python manage.py runserver

Syncs the settings with the Django project: python manage.py migrate

Prepare migrations: python manage.py makemigrations

Create super-user (admin): python manage.py createsuperuser

Create a new app: python manage.py startapp appname

Open Python Shell with Django: python manage.py shell
